{"id":"2ee66e24-a8d3-480b-b002-70e2a1bface7","title":"1548/02: To Lionardo di Buonarroto Simoni","type":"main-list-block","children":[{"id":"4521efc9-5c66-4488-8a0e-4a9ac79af4d6","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"From Rome, February ..., 1548.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"b7a13cb6-7b23-4041-80aa-79029f6c7b8d","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":5,"end":8,"value":"501a8a32-2c8a-4934-9060-8c7e36339f0f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"f1a0ef33-8be5-40de-a604-87dc8c69c50c","type":"codex/time-reference","start":11,"end":28,"value":"7246a16d-7454-452e-80a8-44fcf84955ec","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"a3249135-4612-43ff-bc57-3d5c4ca7e6ed","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"To Lionardo di Buonarroto Simoni,","standoffProperties":[{"id":"d19e7fda-64dc-4af2-a3b7-c4f49abfbb1e","type":"style/italics","start":0,"end":31,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"d2bac41a-fe01-4e1c-b230-86858b3433b2","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":3,"end":31,"value":"93ce2119-f2b8-4642-b551-7b8ca6b1ed96","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"a43e9c2a-986f-462e-b2f1-0bf889c45806","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"in Florence.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"dbf9e160-067e-498c-969a-cfdc81155a47","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":3,"end":10,"value":"671ee7e7-ae1b-4a5a-9591-b40203d5108f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"e50421a2-5d72-4256-a66f-5f08c75dcb20","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"","standoffProperties":[],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"36944474-54a3-4a05-8780-86d9590b84f5","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"Lionardo,\u00A0\u2014\u00A0Since I last wrote to thee I have come across a letter waiting for me in the house here, in which thou givest me an account of all the property that was found belonging to Giovansimone. After that I received another letter in which thou givest me particulars of how he died. As to what he has left, thou mightest have been the first to give me information instead of leaving me to hear of it from others before thee, as was the case. I was excessively indignant about it. As to how he died, thou sayest that although he was not fortified with all the due sacraments of the Church he died, nevertheless, full of penitence. If this is the case it will suffice for the welfare of his soul. Touching the matter of his property, Gismondo is his natural heir as he has made no will: and at the same time I would have thee do as much good as thou canst for the welfare of his soul. Do not stint in the matter of money, for I will not fail thee in whatever thou mayest do. With regard to the contracts and other writings I sent thee, look carefully through them, for they may be of still further use to thee. As to the Corsi house, it seems to me that thou hadst best abide by the offer already made, for if they really desire to sell and matters are as thou sayest, I do not think they will be likely to get more for it in these days. I have nothing more to say.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"d44c9a31-c355-45e3-9305-a228d8356bb2","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":7,"value":"93ce2119-f2b8-4642-b551-7b8ca6b1ed96","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"85134ff7-1774-4803-9289-35151fe08791","type":"style/uppercase","start":0,"end":7,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"76a28eb4-68d6-406f-b1c4-5d6484f2286c","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":18,"end":18,"value":"add92e01-cefe-4f13-94dd-f00eb82155b0","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"151cb131-a699-46ff-9e3e-02ee126a27d2","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":39,"end":39,"value":"add92e01-cefe-4f13-94dd-f00eb82155b0","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"f8b6cfaf-79be-4870-a893-19bcd39b6eb3","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":79,"end":80,"value":"add92e01-cefe-4f13-94dd-f00eb82155b0","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"7e38b638-9d8d-4afc-85e1-127be10bc5c4","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":110,"end":113,"v